Usage   :  run_xDH_using_Gaussian.py [options] FILE

FILE is a Gaussian input with the DFT method being the xDH method (like XYG3, XYGJ-OS, and so on)
The output file shares the same name of FILE with the postfix of 'xDH'


Miscellaneous:
  -v, --version             display version information and exit
      --help                display this help text and exit

Output control:
  -p, --print-level=n       Print option
                            n=1: only summary results are printed (the default choice)
                            n=2: more detailed information are printed
  -g, --gaussian-version=n  The version of the selected Gaussian package
                            n=03: use Gaussian03
                            n=09: use Gaussian09
                            n=16: use Gaussian16 (the default choice)
  -s, --sync-interval=n     The sync interval (in second) between Gaussian and xDH4Gau output files
                            n=12 (the default choice)


1) The reference for the original XYG3 method is
   Zhang, Y.; Xu, X.; Goddard, W. A. Doubly Hybrid Density Functional for
   Accurate Descriptions of Nonbond Interactions, Thermochemistry, and
   Thermochemical Kinetics.
   Proc. Natl. Acad. Sci. USA 2009, 106 (13), 4963-4968.
2) The reference for the lower-scaling XYGJ-OS method is
   Zhang, I. Y.; Xu, X.; Jung, Y.; Goddard, W. A. A Fast Doubly Hybrid Density
   Functional Method Close to Chemical Accuracy Using a Local Opposite Spin Ansatz.
   Proc. Natl. Acad. Sci. USA 2011, 108 (50), 19896-19900.
3) The reference for the family of xDH@B3LYP methods is
   Zhang, I. Y.; Xu, X. Exploring the Limits of the XYG3-Type Doubly Hybrid
   Approximations for the Main-Group Chemistry: The XDH@B3LYP Model.
   J. Phys. Chem. Lett. 2021, 12, 2638-2644.
